According to the text below, who will be responsible for the demurrage?

Dear sirs;
This will serve to remind you that the M/S 'ABC' now discharging Iron Scrapes in bulk at B-25, Pier-4, will have reached the end of her stipulated laydays tomorrow at 10:00. In accordance with the C/P, demurrage will commence at that time and continue until the vessel is wholly discharged, and will be in the sum of Three Thousand Dollars($3,000.00) per day or a fraction thereof, dating from the time demurrage starts. It is expected that you will pay the above mentioned sum daily as long as the vessel remains on demurrage, and I shall call at your office at 15:00 each day to receive payment.
